The solution iterates through the characters of both strings simultaneously using a for loop. It checks if the characters at the same index are equal. If they are equal, the function returns true, indicating that the strings are equal after applying the operations. If no pair of equal characters is found, the function returns false. The time complexity is O(n) because the loop iterates n times, where n is the length of the strings. The space complexity is O(1) because the function uses a constant amount of space for local variables. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs bitwise operations and string comparisons, which are energy-efficient operations.

